Description: OK, THE FINE PRINT, PLEASE READ, as most problems would be avoided by reading the entire listing terms, THANX!!: 1) Please ask any and all questions BEFORE the auction ends, to avoid any disappointment or misunderstandings. 2) I make no warranty claim, and as with all my auctions, all sales are final. I have virtually spotless feedback for a reason. 3) Shipping is $25.00; and is for the continental USA, and will be more outside the lower 48. 4) I do not ship outside the USA, and because of this, you MUST have a USA registered ship to address, AND a USA registered PAYPAL account, no exceptions, as I will NOT ship outside the USA, again, NO EXCEPTIONS!! 5) I do not end auctions early, unless an item is for sale locally on Craigslist, and sells on that site. 6) I expect payment, thru Paypal, within 5 days of auction end, unless PRIOR arrangements have been made with meSQUIER 20th ANNIVERSARY STRATOCASTER GUITAR Here's a Fender Squier 20th Anniversary Stratocaster, in black, with a rosewood fretboard, that comes with the nice padded gig bag pictured. I replaced the 1 ply white pickguard with a Japanese '62 Reissue mint green 3 ply and the matching knobs and pickup covers, as the original had numerous cracks around the mounting screw holes, and was stained. Trem arm is new also. As to the status of this, it has been played, as there are a few dings and chips (pictured), and a small bit of fretwear on several frets. But it does have fast action, quiet pots, solid feel, pretty decent tone and not ice picky, especially for a lower cost guitar. This has real tuners, not the cheap stamped metal cover units, and really, all this would need would maybe a an upgrade of the pickups if you don't care for the tone, or, want to match up with your main axe and use this as a backup. The mint green guard on the black body looks sharp. Frankly, a great platform for your own sonic adventures. Anyway, priced reasonably. Please check pictures for details on physical condition. I've taken pics both with, and without flash to try to better show color, finish and details. Any questions? Please ask now, not later, and thanx for checking out this listing. Thanx for taking a look at this auction, please check my other auctions for vintage gear, pa gear, and a/v equipment among other things. Good luck if you decide to bid!
